column11: I agree to participate in a research study conducted by the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. I...
column12: I understand that this survey will test my reading comprehension (really whether I'm reading at all)...

column108: I want an option between fairly bad and fairly good.
I didn't read the last question about color, which was probably a trick.  So I'm returning the hit

I think when I see the economy shown over a 4 year period, I tend to focus on the last  year as being significant. I also looked at a progression. If it wen't steadily up it was positive, and if it wen't steadily down it was negative.  /  / The 3rd and 4th years especially swayed me to rate how positive or negative the economy was if they were the ones that were up or down.
Because it was the second term, I put equal weight on each year.
I don't know too much about determining whether the economy is "good" or "bad."
Thank you for allowing me to participate.  Thanks for paying me, too.
I wish there were more degrees between the options.  Like a scale of 1-10.
Thank you for the privilege of assisting.
If anyone is making below 40,000.00, something really needs to be done.
Thank you, I don't think I understood the question correctly.

For what it is worth, I looked for upward trends, and over an arbitrary level of income in order for it to be a "good" economy. "Arbitrary" only in that what seems like a lot of money to me is far different from the average person, and all these amounts would be too low to cover my own expenses.
There were an awful lot of economies to look at. I wish I had been warned there were so many.

I think the president has gone a considerable good job considering the mess were in to begin with. I think we are long ways away from being back to "normal" but it's slowly getting better and people are slowly adjusting in my opinion.

Since my income has plummeted ever since Bush seized power, and I am now making 1/4 the amount I was making when Clinton was president, in my opinion, anytime income goes up steadily - even in small amounts - the economy is good. If it goes down at all, the economy may be fair; however, none of the examples you showed amounted to "bad" by any stretch of the imagination according to my experience. With politics as they are and the Republican party and corporate powers attempting to destroy our economy and overthrow the government, I don't think any year in any presidents term of office is predictive of anything. The sabotage is too fierce and unrelenting. Any progress that is made will be immediately destroyed. President Obama has almost no chance of improving the economy or anything else, and when his time is up everything he does manage to do will be destroyed. Just as the economy was in excellent shape and we had a surplus when Clinton left office, then Bush et al trashed everything Clinton had done and threw all our money away, the same thing will happen with president Obama unless we can get the damn Republicans and corporations under control. Nobody could have looked at the economy when Clinton left office and predicted we would be in the sorry state we are in today because nobody expected sabotage.
Thank you and good luck with your study. :-)
way too long a survey for so little pay....kind of disrespectful to your participants
Thanks for letting me particapate in your study,I found it interesting. Hope my responses were helpful.
